{"questionId":"14653","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> for which the graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> is concave-down.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.524 < x < 0.785\\,\\,\\,\\left( {\\frac{\\pi }{6} < x < \\frac{\\pi }{4}} \\right)\">\n  <mn>0.524</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0.785</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mn>6</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2&nbsp; N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if any correct interval outside domain also included, unless additional solutions already penalized in (b).<br>Award<em><strong> A0</strong></em> if any incorrect intervals are also included.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14653","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the values of x for which the graph of f is concave-down.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}